	(text "---------------------------------------------------------\nFIRMWARE & HARDWARE NOTE: MCP23017 INTERRUPT CONFIGURATION\n---------------------------------------------------------\n1. HARDWARE: \n   - INTA pins are routed directly to the backplane (Push-Pull).\n   - INTB pins are intentionally left floating (No Connect).\n   - No external pull-up resistors are required on INTA.\n\n2. FLIGHT SOFTWARE INIT (IOCON Register):\n   - MIRROR = 1 : Merges Port A and Port B interrupts to INTA.\n   - ODR = 0    : Configures INTA as an active Push-Pull output.\n   - INTPOL = x : Set to 0 (Active-Low) or 1 (Active-High) \n                  depending on downstream MCU requirements.\n---------------------------------------------------------"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 216.662 133.858 0)
		(effects
